Gospel artistes across genre, including Tope Alabi, Ada Ehi, Bidemi Olaoba, Mike Abdul, Beejay Sax, Monique, Big Bolaji, and other gifted music ministers, will be at ‘Alimosho Arise’. Also, top comedians like Gordons, Forever rfc, Asiri comedy, and Saco are set to crack people’s ribs with hilarious jokes. The concert, a night of praise, prayer, miracle and salvation, according to a statement, is a night of ‘songfare’ and warfare. The event, which will hold live in Alimosho in Lagos State, on Friday, January 13, 2023, at 8:00 p.m., at Calvary Bible Church, Church Street, end of Anjorin Street, Calvary Bus-Stop, Ikotun-Idimu Road, Lagos, will also be streaming to thousands of viewers all around the world on YouTube and Instagram on @cbcnigeria, with DJ Horphuray and DJ Mordu grinding the wheels of steels. The concert promises to be a night of high-energy praise, worship, and diverse expressions of God with something for everyone.